did.unittitle: St. Alban's "Super Sixties Program" Oral History Project

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Between 1976 and 1979, members of St. Alban's Episcopal church parish conducted over 100 oral history interviews with older residents of the District of Columbia. This project conducted listening interviews in which the interviewee was asked to review their lives and to pass on to others whatever they wished to share of their experience. The project director was Sara Jenkins and it was partly funded by a grant from the Advisory Neighborhood Commission 3-C.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: St. Alban's Parish is an Episcopal church in Washington, D.C. that was founded in 1854.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: St. Alban's Episcopal Church conducted these interviews between 1976 and 1979 and transferred the collection to the Library in the early 1980s. There is no deed of gift for this collection.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: After the initial donation to the Library, the transcripts were placed in folders and stored them in a filing cabinet with other oral histories. Tapes were placed a separate cabinet for patron use. In 2014, the tapes and transcripts were digitized and in 2017 the collection was reprocessed. Transcripts were placed into folders and boxed, while all known tapes were organized and boxed for long term storage. All administrative documents, including releases, were placed into the control file.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: The D.C. Public Library does not hold copyright. It is the responsibility of the researcher to obtain permission from St. Alban's Episcopal Church to publish or exhibit information. Reproduction of oral Histories without release is not permitted.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Materials in this series include transcripts for all interviews.
